		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Alethea Black</strong></span> was born in Boston and graduated from Harvard in 1991. She sometimes eats organic chocolate for breakfast and organic popcorn for dinner. She is the author of the story collection <em>I Knew You’d Be Lovely</em> and the memoir <em>You’ve Been So Lucky Already</em>. When no one could figure out why she was sick, she decided to school herself and now believes all illness has roots in quantum physics — specifically, in the way we experience time.</p><a href="/contributors/alethea-black" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;▸</a>		</div>
